MODULE
     math - Mathematical Functions

DESCRIPTION
     This module provides an interface to a number of  mathemati-
     cal functions.


EXPORTS
     pi() -> float()

          A useful number.

     sin(X)
     cos(X)
     tan(X)
     asin(X)
     acos(X)
     atan(X)
     atan2(X, Y)
     sinh(X)
     cosh(X)
     tanh(X)
     asinh(X)
     acosh(X)
     atanh(X)
     exp(X)
     log(X)
     log10(X)
     pow(X, Y)
     sqrt(X)

          Types
               X = Y = number()

          A collection of math  functions  which  return  floats.
          Arguments are numbers.

     erf(X) -> float()

          Types
               X = number()

          Returns the error function of _X, where

          erf(X) = 2/sqrt(pi)*integral from 0 to X of exp(-t*t) dt.

     erfc(X) -> float()

          Types
               X = number()




